{"title_page": "Victor Skersis", "text_new": "{{Like resume|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox artist\n| name          = Victor Skersis\n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| native_name = \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0421\u043a\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0441\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1956|07|5}}\n| birth_place    = [[Moscow]], Soviet Union\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| residence     = [[Pennsylvania]], United States\n| nationality   = Russian\n| field         =\n| training      =\n| works         = \n| patrons       =\n| awards        =\n| module =\n }}\n\n'''Victor Skersis''' (Russian: \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0410\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0301\u043d\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u043a\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0441, born July 5, 1956, Moscow) \u2014 [[Russian Conceptualism|Moscow conceptualist. Artist, theoretician.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hyperallergic.com/346567/the-disturbingly-relevant-art-of-the-moscow-conceptualists/|title=The Disturbingly Relevant Art of the Moscow Conceptualists|date=2016-12-21|website=Hyperallergic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-11}}</ref>\n{{TOC limit|2}}\n\n== Life and work ==\nStudied at the Moscow State Polygraphic Institute (1973-1977).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.safmuseum.org/artists/skersis.htm|title=Stella Art Foundation. Artist Victor Skersis|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The institute forced him to withdraw two weeks before he was to graduate. Areas of interest include analytical conceptualism, metaconceptualism. An active member of the Moscow art scene since 1975, Skersis works independently and in co-authorship with other artists. He was a member of \"The Nest\" (with Gennady Donskoi and Mikhail Roshal'), 1975-79, \"SZ\" (with Vadim Zakharov), 1980-84, 1989-90, \"Cupid\" (with Yuri Albert and Andrei Filippov), \"Edelweiss\" and \u201cTsar of the Hill\u201d (Yuri Albert, Paruir Davtyan, and Andrei Filippov), and others.\n\nA participant of numerous unofficial art shows in the Soviet Union in the 1970s and 1980s, including the 1975 nonconformist art show in the Culture Pavilion at VDNKh, Moscow; the 1977 Venice Biennale \"La nuova arte Sovietica\"; exhibits at APTART gallery, Moscow 1982-84; \u201cThe Other Art. Moscow 1956-1976,\u201d The Tret'yakov State Gallery, Moscow and The State Russian Museum, Leningrad 1990-1991; \u201c40 years of nonconformist art,\u201d The Central Exhibition Hall Manezh Moscow 2002; \u201cSots-Art. Political art in Russia,\u201d Maison Rouge, Paris, France, The Tret'yakov State Gallery, Moscow, 2007-2008; \u201cKollektsiia,\u201d Pompidou Centre, 2016; \u201cThinking Pictures: Moscow Conceptual Art,\u201d Zimmerli Art Museum, New Brunswick, 2016.\n\nVictor Skersis lives and works in Moscow and the US, where he is engaged in fundamental research into the processes of art.\n\nFrom 1975 to 1979 he was a member of The Nest, together with Gennady Donskoy and Mikhail Roshal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://monoskop.org/Moscow_Conceptualists|title=Moscow Conceptualists - Monoskop|website=monoskop.org|access-date=2019-10-11}}</ref>\n\n== Exhibitions ==\n'''<big>1975</big>'''\n\n* The Nest, House of Culture, VDNKh, Moscow\n\n'''<big>1977</big>'''\n\n* The Nest, Venice Biennale, \"La nuova arte Sovietica\"\n\n=== 1983 ===\n* 1st SZ exhibition (together with Vadim Zakharov).\n* Apt-Art Gallery (Apartment of N. Alekseev), Moscow\n* 2nd SZ exhibition (together with Vadim Zakharov). Apartment M. Roshal, Moscow\n* 3rd SZ exhibition (together with Vadim Zakharov).\n* House of Culture of the 2nd State Bearing Plant on Shabolovka St., Moscow\n* 4th SZ exhibition (traveling, together with Vadim Zakharov). Apartments of N. Alekseev, I. Chuikov, D. Prigov, A. Yulikov, L. Bazhanov, G. Kizevalter, Moscow\n\n=== 1989 === \n* 5th solo exhibition \"SZ\". Organized during the exhibition Muveszet helyet Muveszet, Mucsarnok, Budapest, Hungary\n\n=== 1990 ===\n* Bruder Karamazoff (together with Vadim Zakharov). Sophia Ungers Gallery, Cologne, Germany\n\n=== 2004 ===\n* Group SZ (together with Vadim Zakharov). E.K. Art Bureau, Moscow\n\n=== 2008 ===\n* The Nest Group. National Center for Contemporary Art, Moscow\n* Aspects of meta-art. Project \"Factory\", Moscow\n\n=== 2009 ===\n* Fragma, pragma and enigma (together with Yuri Albert and Andrei Filippov). Project \"Factory\", Moscow\n* Show and Tell. The artist and his model (together with Yuri Albert and Andrei Filippov). Stella Art Foundation, Moscow\n\n=== 2018 ===\n\"Owls are not what they seem\" joint exhibition together with [[Tatyana Sherstyuk]], Gallery 21, [[Moscow Contemporary Art Center Winzavod]], Moscow<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.interiorexplorer.ru/article.php?article=839|title=\u0422\u0430\u043d\u044f \u0428\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0442\u044e\u043a \u0438 \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0421\u043a\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0441. \u0421\u043e\u0432\u044b.|publisher=www.interiorexplorer.ru|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.winzavod.ru/calendar/exhibitions/sovy-ne-to-chem-kazhutsya-/|title=\u0421\u043e\u0432\u044b \u043d\u0435 \u0442\u043e, \u0447\u0435\u043c \u043a\u0430\u0436\u0443\u0442\u0441\u044f - \u0422\u0430\u043d\u044f \u0428\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0442\u044e\u043a, \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0421\u043a\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0441|publisher=\u0412\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://artguide.com/events/13830|title=\u0421\u043e\u0432\u044b \u043d\u0435 \u0442\u043e, \u0447\u0435\u043c \u043a\u0430\u0436\u0443\u0442\u0441\u044f|publisher=\u0410\u0440\u0442\u0433\u0438\u0434|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theartnewspaper.ru/posts/6004/|title=\u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0438 \u0441\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044f\u0431\u0440\u044f \u0432 \u0433\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0440\u0435\u044f\u0445 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b|author=\u0415\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u0430\u0433\u043d\u0435\u0440|date=2018-08-31|publisher=The Art Newspaper Russia|language=ru|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref><ref name=\u0412\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0435>{{cite web|url=https://www.mk.ru/culture/2018/09/18/na-vinzavode-veneru-prevratili-v-zayca.html|title=\u041d\u0430 \"\u0412\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0435\" \u0412\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0443 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u0437\u0430\u0439\u0446\u0430|publisher=www.mk.ru|language=ru|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gallery-21.ru/exhibitions/sovi-ne-to_-chem-kazhutsia/|title=\u0421\u043e\u0432\u044b \u043d\u0435 \u0442\u043e, \u0447\u0435\u043c \u043a\u0430\u0436\u0443\u0442\u0441\u044f \u2014 \u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0438 \u2014 Gallery 21 \u2014 \u0413\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0440\u0435\u044f 21|publisher=www.gallery-21.ru|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref>\n[[File:\u0422\u0430\u0442\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0430_\u0428\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0442\u044e\u043a_\u0438_\u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440_\u0421\u043a\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0441_\u0434\u043b\u044f_\"\u0421\u043e\u0432\u044b_-_\u043d\u0435_\u0442\u043e,_\u0447\u0435\u043c_\u043a\u0430\u0436\u0443\u0442\u0441\u044f\"._\u0424\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u044f_\u041d\u0430\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438_\u0422\u0430\u0437\u0431\u0430\u0448.jpg|thumb]]\n{{Quote|text=Nike is losing her head at the date with a snowman. Venus is exchanging her shadow with Apollo where the shadow turns into a rabbit, and after into a duck\u2026These narratives are rhythmed and turn into a poetry of a size of a gallery. They fly of like a refrain by the exhibition of two artists of different generations \u2013 a legendary Victor Skersis from art team \"Nest\" and a young inheritor of \"Analytical conceptualism\": Tatyana Sherstyuk. A poem written by with spectacular illusions is named \"Owls are not what they seem\". Maria Moskvicheva (a journalist, an historian, a culturologist, an art columnist of Moskovky Kmsololets Newspaper, a member of Association of Art Critics (AIS).<ref name=\u0412\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0435/>}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n<references responsive=\"\" />\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Skersis, Victor}}\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Artists from Moscow]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Russian contemporary artists]]\n\n\n{{improve categories|date=October 2019}}\n", "text_old": "{{Like resume|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox artist\n| name          = Victor Skersis\n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| native_name = \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0421\u043a\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0441\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1956|07|5}}\n| birth_place    = [[Moscow]], Soviet Union\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| residence     = [[Pennsylvania]], United States\n| nationality   = Russian\n| field         =\n| training      =\n| works         = \n| patrons       =\n| awards        =\n| module =\n }}\n\n'''Victor Skersis''' (Russian: \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0410\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0301\u043d\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u043a\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0441, born July 5, 1956, Moscow) \u2014 [[Russian Conceptualism|Moscow conceptualist. Artist, theoretician.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hyperallergic.com/346567/the-disturbingly-relevant-art-of-the-moscow-conceptualists/|title=The Disturbingly Relevant Art of the Moscow Conceptualists|date=2016-12-21|website=Hyperallergic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-11}}</ref>\n{{TOC limit|2}}\n\n== Life and work ==\nStudied at the Moscow State Polygraphic Institute (1973-1977).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.safmuseum.org/artists/skersis.htm|title=Stella Art Foundation. Artist Victor Skersis|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The institute forced him to withdraw two weeks before he was to graduate. Artist, theoretician. Areas of interest include analytical conceptualism, metaconceptualism. An active member of the Moscow art scene since 1975, Skersis works independently and in co-authorship with other artists. He was a member of \"The Nest\" (with Gennady Donskoi and Mikhail Roshal'), primarily active from 1975-79, \"SZ\" (with Vadim Zakharov), primarily active from 1980-84, 1990, \"Cupid\" (with Yuri Albert and Andrei Filippov), ongoing, \"Edelweiss\" and \u201cTsar of the Hill\u201d (Yuri Albert, Paruir Davtyan, and Andrei Filippov), ongoing, and others.\n\nA participant of numerous unofficial art shows in the Soviet Union in the 1970s and 1980s, including the 1975 nonconformist art show in the Culture Pavilion at VDNKh, Moscow, the 1977 Venice Biennale \"La nuova arte Sovietica\"; exhibits at APTART gallery, Moscow 1982-84; \u201cThe Other Art. Moscow 1956-1976,\u201d The Tret'yakov State Gallery, Moscow and The State Russian Museum, Leningrad 1990-1991; \u201c40 years of nonconformist art,\u201d The Central Exhibition Hall Manezh Moscow 2002; \u201cSots-Art. Political art in Russia,\u201d Maison Rouge, Paris, France, The Tret'yakov State Gallery, Moscow, 2007-2008; \u201cKollektsiia,\u201d Pompidou Centre, 2016; \u201cThinking Pictures: Moscow Conceptual Art,\u201d Zimmerli Art Museum, New Brunswick, 2016.\n\nVictor Skersis lives and works in Moscow and the US, where he is engaged in fundamental research into the processes of art.\n\nFrom 1975 to 1979 he was a member of The Nest, together with Gennady Donskoy and Mikhail Roshal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://monoskop.org/Moscow_Conceptualists|title=Moscow Conceptualists - Monoskop|website=monoskop.org|access-date=2019-10-11}}</ref>\n\n== Exhibitions ==\n'''<big>1975</big>'''\n\n* The Nest, House of Culture, VDNKh, Moscow\n\n'''<big>1977</big>'''\n\n* The Nest, Venice Biennale, \"La nuova arte Sovietica\"\n\n=== 1983 ===\n* 1st SZ exhibition (together with Vadim Zakharov).\n* Apt-Art Gallery (Apartment of N. Alekseev), Moscow\n* 2nd SZ exhibition (together with Vadim Zakharov). Apartment M. Roshal, Moscow\n* 3rd SZ exhibition (together with Vadim Zakharov).\n* House of Culture of the 2nd State Bearing Plant on Shabolovka St., Moscow\n* 4th SZ exhibition (traveling, together with Vadim Zakharov). Apartments of N. Alekseev, I. Chuikov, D. Prigov, A. Yulikov, L. Bazhanov, G. Kizevalter, Moscow\n\n=== 1989 === \n* 5th solo exhibition \"SZ\". Organized during the exhibition Muveszet helyet Muveszet, Mucsarnok, Budapest, Hungary\n\n=== 1990 ===\n* Bruder Karamazoff (together with Vadim Zakharov). Sophia Ungers Gallery, Cologne, Germany\n\n=== 2004 ===\n* Group SZ (together with Vadim Zakharov). E.K. Art Bureau, Moscow\n\n=== 2008 ===\n* The Nest Group. National Center for Contemporary Art, Moscow\n* Aspects of meta-art. Project \"Factory\", Moscow\n\n=== 2009 ===\n* Fragma, pragma and enigma (together with Yuri Albert and Andrei Filippov). Project \"Factory\", Moscow\n* Show and Tell. The artist and his model (together with Yuri Albert and Andrei Filippov). Stella Art Foundation, Moscow\n\n=== 2018 ===\n\"Owls are not what they seem\" joint exhibition together with [[Tatyana Sherstyuk]], Gallery 21, [[Moscow Contemporary Art Center Winzavod]], Moscow<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.interiorexplorer.ru/article.php?article=839|title=\u0422\u0430\u043d\u044f \u0428\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0442\u044e\u043a \u0438 \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0421\u043a\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0441. \u0421\u043e\u0432\u044b.|publisher=www.interiorexplorer.ru|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.winzavod.ru/calendar/exhibitions/sovy-ne-to-chem-kazhutsya-/|title=\u0421\u043e\u0432\u044b \u043d\u0435 \u0442\u043e, \u0447\u0435\u043c \u043a\u0430\u0436\u0443\u0442\u0441\u044f - \u0422\u0430\u043d\u044f \u0428\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0442\u044e\u043a, \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0421\u043a\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0441|publisher=\u0412\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://artguide.com/events/13830|title=\u0421\u043e\u0432\u044b \u043d\u0435 \u0442\u043e, \u0447\u0435\u043c \u043a\u0430\u0436\u0443\u0442\u0441\u044f|publisher=\u0410\u0440\u0442\u0433\u0438\u0434|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theartnewspaper.ru/posts/6004/|title=\u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0438 \u0441\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044f\u0431\u0440\u044f \u0432 \u0433\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0440\u0435\u044f\u0445 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b|author=\u0415\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u0430\u0433\u043d\u0435\u0440|date=2018-08-31|publisher=The Art Newspaper Russia|language=ru|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref><ref name=\u0412\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0435>{{cite web|url=https://www.mk.ru/culture/2018/09/18/na-vinzavode-veneru-prevratili-v-zayca.html|title=\u041d\u0430 \"\u0412\u0438\u043d\u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0435\" \u0412\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0443 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u0437\u0430\u0439\u0446\u0430|publisher=www.mk.ru|language=ru|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gallery-21.ru/exhibitions/sovi-ne-to_-chem-kazhutsia/|title=\u0421\u043e\u0432\u044b \u043d\u0435 \u0442\u043e, \u0447\u0435\u043c \u043a\u0430\u0436\u0443\u0442\u0441\u044f \u2014 \u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0438 \u2014 Gallery 21 \u2014 \u0413\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0440\u0435\u044f 21|publisher=www.gallery-21.ru|accessdate=2018-12-06}}</ref>\n[[File:\u0422\u0430\u0442\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0430_\u0428\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0442\u044e\u043a_\u0438_\u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440_\u0421\u043a\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0441_\u0434\u043b\u044f_\"\u0421\u043e\u0432\u044b_-_\u043d\u0435_\u0442\u043e,_\u0447\u0435\u043c_\u043a\u0430\u04